result.execSummary:
The defendant Joshua Dubois Yarbrough was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Charges per attached criminal complaint. Conditions:   It is a condition of this bond that the defendant NOT consume or possess any controlled substances.  This is to be monitored by random UA's and/or breathalyzers.  The defendant is to report directly to Zimmerman Consulting Inc. (ZCI) for monitoring - report to 524 Main Street, Suite 302, Racine, WI  53403 (third floor of the Monument Square Building) or call (262)632-1780 to immediately schedule an appointment.   The defendant is further ordered to report for testing after each court appearance.  Defendant to be placed on GPS monitor through Zimmerman Consulting Inc. (ZCI), 524 Main Street, 3rd floor, (262-632-1780).  Defendant must attend 7 self-help meetings per week and provide signed proof of attendance.  Make all court appearances on time.  Failure to appear will result in the issuance of a warrant for your arrest, possible bail jumping charges and forfeiture of any bond on deposit.

AMENDED 04-04-2017: GPS MAY BE REMOVED. DEFENDANT TO MAKE PAYMENTS TO RCAP EACH WEEK.

Defendant Joshua Dubois Yarbrough in court with attorney Laura Ann Walker.  Jennifer Tanck-Adams appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Darlene Shue.
Also present is Boyd Schwartz from RCAP indicating deft has not made the substantial payment toward his fees as ordered by the Court. Defense indicates that deft wishes Ms. Walker to withdraw.

BTC: Ms. Walker's motion to withdraw is denied. Modify bond to GPS may be removed. Defendant is to make payments every week to RCAP  Jury trial scheduled for April 25, 2017 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Joshua Dubois Yarbrough in court with attorney Laura Ann Walker.  Jennifer Tanck-Adams appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Darlene Shue.
Matter has been in trial posture for some time but it has not gone yet. Defense indicates she reiterated the final offer this morning and she asks for a short turn around to allow deft time to reconsider the offer.
Defense indicates that she is understanding that RCAP is asking that deft be removed from GPS and that he has no violations that she is aware of. The Court notes 2 violations and indicates that RCAP is going to remove the bracelet due to non payment and if they do, that would render him in violation of his bond. Defense indicates deft cannot afford GPS. The State does not object to GPS being removed.

BTC: GPS may not be removed. The deft is admonished to make payments toward GPS or bond will be modified on the Courts own motion. Status conference scheduled for April 4, 2017 at 08:30 am.
